        "title": "Who are the best Liverpool picks in FPL for their strong fixtures?",
        "description": "The Scout assesses who to target from Jurgen Kloppâ€™s side for favourable long-term schedule",
        "content": "<p>The Scout pinpoints the clubs and players to target for the upcoming period in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://fantasy.premierleague.com/\">Fantasy Premier League.</a></p>\n<h6><a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/10/Liverpool/overview\">Liverpool</a></h6>\n<p>Jurgen Klopp&rsquo;s side are set for an extended run of kind opponents that lifts their prospects in Fantasy for many Gameweeks ahead.</p>\n<p>According to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://fantasy.premierleague.com/fixtures/fdr\">Fixture Difficulty Ratings</a>&nbsp;(FDR), six of Liverpool&rsquo;s next eight matches score only two.</p>\n<p>That includes a run of matches against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/7/Everton/overview\">Everton</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/15/Nottingham-Forest/overview\">Nottingham Forest</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/163/Luton-Town/overview\">Luton Town</a>&nbsp;in the next three Gameweeks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>That fixture run gives&nbsp;<strong>Mohamed Salah</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;12.6m) the chance to bring in more huge hauls.</p>\n<p>The Egyptian&rsquo;s 15-point return against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/131/Brighton-and-Hove-Albion/overview\">Brighton &amp; Hove Albion</a>&nbsp;in Gameweek 8 took him to 59 points for the season, joint-top in the player standings.</p>\n<p>Salah has delivered double-figure scores in three of Liverpool&rsquo;s last four, highlighting his major potential as an armband contender to&nbsp;<strong>Erling Haaland</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;14.0m).</p>\n<p>The Reds&rsquo; talisman has also been among the most consistent players in 2023/24 Fantasy, blanking in only one of his eight appearances.</p>\n<p>Unsurprisingly, Salah dominates the goal threat numbers, ranking top for shots, shots in the box, shots on target and goals for Liverpool.</p>\n<h6>Who's the second-best attacker?</h6>\n<p><strong>Darwin Nunez</strong>&rsquo;s (&pound;7.4m) statistics show why he could be a big success if he can secure a regular role. Despite starting only three matches, the Uruguay forward has recorded a team-leading eight big chances.</p>\n<p>His numbers fare well when compared with those of&nbsp;<strong>Luis Diaz</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;7.5m), who has started seven fixtures on the left.</p>\n<p>Nunez has matched the Colombian&rsquo;s 17 shots, has had double the number of big chances, and has also bettered his team-mate for both shots on target and goals.</p>\n<p><strong>See:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/news/3734930\">FPL experts' plans for Liverpool players</a></strong></p>\n<p>Although summer signing&nbsp;<strong>Dominik Szoboszlai</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;7.0m) also features highly for overall shots, only two of his 15 efforts have been from inside the opposition box.</p>\n<h6>Liverpool&rsquo;s top goal threats compared</h6>",
