        "id": 33,
        "title": "Keep or sell Son and Maddison in FPL from Gameweek 10?",
        "description": "The Scout says there is a clear player to ditch as Spurs' fixtures take a turn. Here's what the data tells us",
        "content": "<p>The Scout pinpoints the clubs and players to target for the upcoming period in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://fantasy.premierleague.com/\">Fantasy Premier League</a>.</p>\n<h6><a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/21/Tottenham-Hotspur/overview\">Tottenham Hotspur</a></h6>\n<p>Owners of&nbsp;<strong>Son Heung-min</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;9.5m) and&nbsp;<strong>James Maddison</strong>&nbsp;(&pound;8.1m) in Fantasy are facing a major decision in the coming Gameweeks, with a host of midfielders from other clubs offering kinder runs of opponents.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>See:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/news/3734945\">What FPL experts are doing with Spurs players</a></strong></p>\n<p>The Spurs pair are among the five most-selected midfielders, found in 38 and 34 per cent of squads respectively.</p>\n<p>Both have enjoyed strong starts under new head coach Ange Postecoglou this season. Son ranks fourth overall in the FPL scoring charts, on 54 points, while Maddison has amassed 47 points.</p>\n<p>However, a swing in schedule difficulty from Gameweek 10 in favour of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/1/Arsenal/overview\">Arsenal</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/131/Brighton-and-Hove-Albion/overview\">Brighton &amp; Hove Albion</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/25/West-Ham-United/overview\">West Ham United</a>&nbsp;could persuade many managers to consider selling the Spurs pair.</p>\n<p><strong>See:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/news/3733342\">Why GW10 is a great time to Wildcard</a></strong></p>\n<h6>Hold for the short term</h6>\n<p>Spurs&rsquo; short-term schedule at least looks encouraging for more returns.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>According to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://fantasy.premierleague.com/fixtures/fdr\">Fixture Difficulty Ratings</a>&nbsp;(FDR), three of their next four matches, against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/34/Fulham/overview\">Fulham</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/6/Crystal-Palace/overview\">Crystal Palace</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.premierleague.com/clubs/38/Wolverhampton-Wanderers/overview\">Wolverhampton Wanderers</a>, score only two.</p>\n<p>Son heads into this period on the back of six goals in five matches since being moved up front in Gameweek 4.</p>\n<p>Indeed, the South Korean is the top-scoring player in Fantasy over that run, amassing 46 points to the 25 of Maddison.</p>",
        "image": "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/lmproject-538b3.appspot.com/o/news%2FMaddison-Son.webp?alt=media&token=0f5a9cc2-6888-49df-abf5-366c016c4db8",
